        public static PortInfo fromSubPort(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Port port,
                                   org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Port subPort)
        Create a new port info for a combination of Port and sub-port. Compared to the constructor, the order of sub and parent port is inverted. The function is useful, if the sub-port is optional
        Parameters:
        port - a port
        subPort - an optional supPort.

      • getModelPort

        public org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Port getModelPort()
        Returns:
        Return the port of the original model, i.e. the parent port, if the port is actually a sub-port or the original port, if it is not. This function is useful for testing delegation relationships (which could not exist for a sub-port)
